{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871385552,"sessionID":"ses_285d19579ffenKhkYlggxpkabA","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2edcb30011JyHEE3s9fYkF7","messageID":"msg_d7a2ecad10016cY0v6Bq08uEfX","sessionID":"ses_285d19579ffenKhkYlggxpkabA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f19fe9450e85403783fc6aade961651a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-022 |\n8: | Module | cmd/cli |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Implement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n17: \n18: **Current State**: CLI has `pack` and `build` commands that generate Dockerfile and build container images, but no deployment capability. Users must manually push images and create Kubernetes resources.\n19: \n20: **Target State**: \n21: - Single `kubectl-agentcube publish` command that deploys agents to Kubernetes\n22: - Support for two providers: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service)\n23: - Automatic image preparation via Docker push or explicit image URL\n24: - Metadata updated with deployment info, agent_id, and endpoint URLs\n25: - Namespace, replicas, and NodePort configuration support\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n30: \n31: ### 2.1 In Scope\n32: \n33: | Deliverable | Description |\n34: |-------------|-------------|\n35: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` class with publish orchestration logic |\n36: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | `publish` Typer command with CLI options |\n37: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` for standard K8s Deployment/Service |\n38: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR deployment |\n39: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Image push methods (extends AR-021) |\n40: \n41: ### 2.2 PublishRuntime Methods\n42: \n43: | Method | Purpose |\n44: |--------|---------|\n45: | `publish(workspace_path, **options)` | Main orchestration entry point |\n46: | `_publish_cr_to_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, **options)` | Deploy via AgentCube AgentRuntime CR |\n47: | `_publish_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, **options)` | Deploy via standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service |\n48: | `_prepare_image_for_publishing(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Image preparation (push or URL) |\n49: | `_prepare_local_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Push local Docker image to registry |\n50: | `_prepare_cloud_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Use cloud-built image URL |\n51: | `_update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, agent_info)` | Persist deployment info to metadata YAML |\n52: \n53: ### 2.3 CLI Options\n54: \n55: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n56: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n57: | `--workspace` / `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace directory |\n58: | `--version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n59: | `--image-url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n60: | `--image-username` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Username for image repository |\n61: | `--image-password` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Password for image repository |\n62: | `--description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n63: | `--region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n64: | `--cloud-provider` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n65: | `--provider` | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n66: | `--node-port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s |\n67: | `--replicas` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Number of replicas (default: 1) |\n68: | `--namespace` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Kubernetes namespace |\n69: | `--verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n70: \n71: ### 2.4 Out of Scope\n72: \n73: | Item | Reason |\n74: |------|--------|\n75: | Cloud publish implementation | Requires cloud provider SDK integration; placeholder only |\n76: | Helm chart deployment | Different deployment paradigm; future enhancement |\n77: | Auto-scaling configuration | Not specified in requirements; HPA would be separate feature |\n78: | Secret management | Beyond current scope; requires vault integration |\n79: | Multi-cluster deployment | Requires federation setup; future enhancement |\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n84: \n85: ### 3.1 新增文件\n86: \n87: ```\n88: cmd/cli/\n89: ├── agentcube/\n90: │   ├── runtime/\n91: │   │   └── publish_runtime.py     # PublishRuntime class\n92: │   ├── services/\n93: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py        # KubernetesProvider class\n94: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py  # AgentCubeProvider class\n95: │   │   └── docker_service.py      # (extend with push_image)\n96: │   └── cli/\n97: │       └── main.py                # publish command (addition to existing)\n98: └── tests/\n99:     ├── test_publish_runtime.py    # Unit tests for PublishRuntime\n100:     ├── test_k8s_provider.py       # Unit tests for KubernetesProvider\n101:     └── test_agentcube_provider.py # Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider\n102: ```\n103: \n104: ### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n105: \n106: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n107: |------------|---------|--------|\n108: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Python client for Kubernetes API; optional dependency under `[k8s]` extras |\n109: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push operations |\n110: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n111: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and table output |\n112: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n113: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future cloud integration |\n114: \n115: ### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n116: \n117: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n118: |----------|--------------|\n119: | `invoke` command | Uses agent_endpoint from metadata for HTTP calls |\n120: | `status` command | Reads k8s_deployment info from metadata |\n121: | `pack`/`build` commands | Provide image info for publish flow |\n122: | Users | CLI invocation `kubectl-agentcube publish -f ./my-agent` |\n123: \n124: ### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n125: \n126: - **Metadata schema**: Adding `k8s_deployment` field with sub-fields (`type`, `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `service_url`, `agent_id`)\n127: - **Provider parameter**: New `--provider` flag changes behavior significantly\n128: - **AgentRuntime CR dependency**: Requires Volcano AgentCube CRD installed for `agentcube` provider\n129: - **Registry credentials**: Password passed via CLI flag (insecure); recommend env vars or secret files\n130: \n131: ### 3.5 Compatibility Notes\n132: \n133: - Kubernetes client `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()` reads from `~/.kube/config` by default\n134: - NodePort range must be 30000-32767 per Kubernetes specification\n135: - AgentRuntime CR uses API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n136: - Image URL format: `{registry}/{repository}/{image}:{tag}`\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n141: \n142: ### Alternative 1: Direct kubectl Execution\n143: \n144: **Approach**: Generate YAML manifests and execute `kubectl apply` via `subprocess.run()`.\n145: \n146: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n147: |--------|------------|\n148: | Pros | Familiar to K8s users; no Python SDK dependency |\n149: | Cons | No programmatic status checks; harder error parsing; platform-specific; no wait-for-ready logic |\n150: \n151: **Decision**: Rejected. Kubernetes Python SDK provides typed API, wait loops, and structured status retrieval.\n152: \n153: ### Alternative 2: Helm Chart Publishing\n154: \n155: **Approach**: Package agent as Helm chart and use `helm install` for deployment.\n156: \n157: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n158: |--------|------------|\n159: | Pros | Standard K8s packaging; templating support; versioning built-in |\n160: | Cons | Requires Helm CLI; additional complexity; not in original spec |\n161: \n162: **Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. May add as alternative publishing mode in future.\n163: \n164: ### Alternative 3: Separate Push and Deploy Commands\n165: \n166: **Approach**: Split into `push-image` and `deploy` commands instead of unified `publish`.\n167: \n168: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n169: |--------|------------|\n170: | Pros | More granular control; can push without deploying |\n171: | Cons | More commands to learn; friction in typical workflow |\n172: \n173: **Decision**: Rejected. Unified `publish` command matches spec requirements and provides smoother user experience.\n174: \n175: ### Alternative 4: Docker Compose for Local Testing\n176: \n177: **Approach**: Support Docker Compose as deployment target for local development.\n178: \n179: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n180: |--------|------------|\n181: | Pros | Easy local testing; no K8s required |\n182: | Cons | Different networking model; not production-ready |\n183: \n184: **Decision**: Rejected. Focus on Kubernetes deployment per spec; local testing via `docker run` sufficient.\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## 5. Risks\n189: \n190: | Risk | Mitigation |\n191: |------|------------|\n192: | Kubernetes cluster unreachable | Load kubeconfig first; fail early with clear error message |\n193: | AgentRuntime CRD not installed | `AgentCubeProvider` checks CR existence; raises `ValueError` if not found |\n194: | Missing router_url/workload_manager_url for agentcube | Validation in `_publish_cr_to_k8s` raises `ValueError` |\n195: | Image push auth failure | `DockerService._docker_login_sdk` handles credentials; log warning on failure |\n196: | Deployment timeout | `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready(timeout=120)` raises `TimeoutError` |\n197: | NodePort collision | K8s auto-assigns if NodePort not specified; validation for range 30000-32767 |\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n202: \n203: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.__init__()` with namespace, kubeconfig options\n204: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._ensure_namespace()` to create namespace if missing\n205: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` for Deployment + Service creation\n206: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._create_deployment()` with sanitization, env_vars\n207: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._create_service()` with NodePort handling\n208: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready()` with timeout loop\n209: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` for pod/deployment status\n210: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent()` for cleanup\n211: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._sanitize_name()` for K8s name compliance\n212: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.__init__()` with namespace, kubeconfig options\n213: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider._ensure_namespace()` \n214: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` for AgentRuntime CR\n215: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name()` for CR name compliance\n216: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()` for CR status retrieval\n217: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime.publish()` orchestration entry point\n218: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` for AgentCube provider\n219: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s()` for standard K8s provider\n220: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing()` image preparation\n221: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` Docker push logic\n222: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_cloud_image()` cloud image URL handling\n223: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata()` metadata persistence\n224: - [ ] Add `publish` Typer command in `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n225: - [ ] Add error handling with `_handle_error()` for verbose traceback\n226: - [ ] Add Rich `Progress` spinner for publish status\n227: - [ ] Add `k8s_deployment` and `agent_id` fields to `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n228: - [ ] Unit tests for KubernetesProvider mock K8s API\n229: - [ ] Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider mock CR API\n230: - [ ] Unit tests for image preparation logic\n231: - [ ] Integration test for full publish workflow (mocked)\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ## 7. References\n236: \n237: - Spec: `changes/AR-022/spec.md`\n238: - Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n239: - CLI Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Requirement: `publish` command\n240: - Deployment Spec: `deployment/spec.md` — Kubernetes deployment patterns\n241: - Python SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md` — AgentRuntimeClient integration\n242: - AR-021 — CLI build command (image preparation dependency)\n243: - Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n244: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n245: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-022 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | L |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nImplement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n\n**Current State**: CLI has `pack` and `build` commands that generate Dockerfile and build container images, but no deployment capability. Users must manually push images and create Kubernetes resources.\n\n**Target State**: ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871385531,"end":1775871385550}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871385556,"sessionID":"ses_285d19579ffenKhkYlggxpkabA","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2edfa7001IpHHk6jOGBXRHr","messageID":"msg_d7a2ecad10016cY0v6Bq08uEfX","sessionID":"ses_285d19579ffenKhkYlggxpkabA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4209861ab6eb4911a51179380b42cfe2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n2: \n3: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Implement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Publish Command Entry Point\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a `publish` subcommand via Typer application to deploy agents to Kubernetes with provider selection.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Options and Defaults\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish` without specifying any options\n24: - **WHEN** the command is invoked\n25: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n26:   - `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, type `str`)\n27:   - `version` = `None` (`--version`, type `Optional[str]`)\n28:   - `image_url` = `None` (`--image-url`, type `Optional[str]`)\n29:   - `image_username` = `None` (`--image-username`, type `Optional[str]`)\n30:   - `image_password` = `None` (`--image-password`, type `Optional[str]`)\n31:   - `description` = `None` (`--description`, type `Optional[str]`)\n32:   - `region` = `None` (`--region`, type `Optional[str]`)\n33:   - `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`, type `Optional[str]`)\n34:   - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`, type `str`)\n35:   - `node_port` = `None` (`--node-port`, type `Optional[int]`)\n36:   - `replicas` = `None` (`--replicas`, type `Optional[int]`)\n37:   - `namespace` = `None` (`--namespace`, type `Optional[str]`)\n38:   - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, type `bool`)\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Successful Publish with AgentCube Provider\n41: \n42: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace with metadata containing `agent_name`, `image`, `router_url`, and `workload_manager_url`\n43: - **WHEN** `publish` completes with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n44: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n45:   - Display a Rich Progress spinner during execution\n46:   - Print success message including `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, and deployment type\n47:   - Exit with code `0`\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Successful Publish with Kubernetes Provider\n50: \n51: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace with metadata containing `agent_name`, `image`, and Kubernetes cluster accessible\n52: - **WHEN** `publish` completes with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n53: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n54:   - Display a Rich Progress spinner during execution\n55:   - Print success message including `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `node_port`, and `service_url`\n56:   - Exit with code `0`\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Publish Failure Handling with Verbose\n59: \n60: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` raises an exception\n61: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n62: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n63:   - Print `Error publishing agent: {e}` in red via Rich\n64:   - Print the full traceback\n65:   - Exit with code `1`\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Publish Failure Handling without Verbose\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` raises an exception\n70: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `False`\n71: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n72:   - Print `Error publishing agent: {e}` in red via Rich\n73:   - Exit with code `1` without printing traceback\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: PublishRuntime Initialization\n78: \n79: The system SHALL construct `PublishRuntime` with provider selection.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: PublishRuntime Constructor Default Provider\n82: \n83: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime(verbose=False)` is constructed\n84: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n85: - **THEN** the runtime SHALL:\n86:   - Set `provider` to `\"agentcube\"` (default)\n87:   - Initialize `MetadataService` for metadata operations\n88:   - Initialize `DockerService` for image push operations\n89:   - Store the `verbose` flag for logging control\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: PublishRuntime Constructor Explicit Provider\n92: \n93: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime(verbose=False, provider=\"k8s\")` is constructed\n94: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n95: - **THEN** the runtime SHALL:\n96:   - Set `provider` to `\"k8s\"`\n97:   - Initialize `KubernetesProvider` with default namespace `\"default\"`\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: PublishRuntime.publish Orchestration\n102: \n103: The system SHALL orchestrate the publish workflow with validation, image preparation, deployment, and metadata update.\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Load Metadata from Workspace\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n108: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish(workspace_path, **options)` runs\n109: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n110:   - Call `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)`\n111:   - Validate metadata has required `agent_name` and `image` fields\n112:   - Raise `ValueError` if metadata is missing required fields\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Apply CLI Option Overrides\n115: \n116: - **GIVEN** metadata loaded from workspace\n117: - **WHEN** CLI options are provided\n118: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n119:   - Override `metadata.version` if `--version` is provided\n120:   - Override `metadata.description` if `--description` is provided\n121:   - Override `metadata.region` if `--region` is provided\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Provider Selection Branching\n124: \n125: - **GIVEN** `provider` option is set\n126: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` determines deployment method\n127: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n128:   - Call `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` if `provider == \"agentcube\"`\n129:   - Call `_publish_k8s()` if `provider == \"k8s\"`\n130:   - Raise `ValueError` if `provider` is neither `\"agentcube\"` nor `\"k8s\"`\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ### Requirement: Image Preparation\n135: \n136: The system SHALL prepare the container image for deployment via Docker push or explicit URL.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Prepare Image for Publishing\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `build_mode`\n141: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing()` runs\n142: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n143:   - Call `_prepare_local_image()` if `build_mode == \"local\"`\n144:   - Call `_prepare_cloud_image()` if `build_mode == \"cloud\"`\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Prepare Local Image with Registry\n147: \n148: - **GIVEN** `build_mode == \"local\"` and `image_url` is provided\n149: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` runs\n150: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n151:   - Call `DockerService.push_image()` with registry URL and credentials\n152:   - Return the pushed image URL `{registry_url}/{agent_name}:{version}`\n153:   - Raise `RuntimeError` if Docker push fails\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: Prepare Local Image Missing URL\n156: \n157: - **GIVEN** `build_mode == \"local\"` and `image_url` is not provided\n158: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` runs\n159: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating `--image-url` is required for local build mode\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Prepare Cloud Image URL\n162: \n163: - **GIVEN** `build_mode == \"cloud\"` and `cloud_provider` is provided\n164: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_cloud_image()` runs\n165: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n166:   - Return the image URL from `metadata.image` field\n167:   - Log warning if cloud publish is not fully implemented\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: AgentCube Provider Prerequisites\n172: \n173: The system SHALL validate required fields before deploying via AgentCube provider.\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Validate Router URL\n176: \n177: - **GIVEN** `provider == \"agentcube\"` and `metadata.router_url` is `None` or empty\n178: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` runs\n179: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring `router_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Validate Workload Manager URL\n182: \n183: - **GIVEN** `provider == \"agentcube\"` and `metadata.workload_manager_url` is `None` or empty\n184: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` runs\n185: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring `workload_manager_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Validate Readiness Probe Fields\n188: \n189: - **GIVEN** `provider == \"agentcube\"`\n190: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` runs\n191: - **THEN** the system SHALL use:\n192:   - `metadata.readiness_probe_path` or default `\"/health\"`\n193:   - `metadata.readiness_probe_port` or `metadata.port`\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ### Requirement: AgentCube Provider Deployment\n198: \n199: The system SHALL deploy via AgentRuntime CR to Kubernetes.\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: AgentCubeProvider Initialization\n202: \n203: - **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider(namespace=\"default\", verbose=False)`\n204: - **WHEN** the provider is constructed\n205: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n206:   - Load kubeconfig via `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()`\n207:   - Initialize CustomObjectApi client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n208:   - Set namespace to `\"default\"` or provided value\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Ensure Namespace Exists\n211: \n212: - **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider` is initialized\n213: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` runs\n214: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n215:   - Check if namespace exists via `CoreV1Api.read_namespace()`\n216:   - Create namespace if it does not exist\n217:   - Log creation in verbose mode\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n220: \n221: - **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` is called\n222: - **WHEN** the CR is created\n223: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n224:   - Create CustomObject with `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`\n225:   - Set CR name via `_sanitize_name(agent_name)` (lowercase, DNS compliant)\n226:   - Set `spec.image` to image URL\n227:   - Set `spec.port` to metadata port\n228:   - Set `spec.sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"`\n229:   - Set `spec.maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`\n230:   - Set `spec.imagePullSecrets` to `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n231:   - Embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` in `spec.env` when provided\n232:   - Return result dict with `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `deployment_name`\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: Sanitize Name for CR\n235: \n236: - **GIVEN** `agent_name` contains special characters or uppercase\n237: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name(agent_name)` runs\n238: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n239:   - Convert to lowercase\n240:   - Replace invalid characters with `-`\n241:   - Truncate to 63 characters if exceeds Kubernetes name limit\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Patch Existing AgentRuntime CR\n244: \n245: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR with the same name already exists\n246: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime()` runs\n247: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n248:   - Use `patch_custom_object` instead of `create_custom_object`\n249:   - Update image, port, and environment variables\n250:   - Return updated CR info\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ### Requirement: Kubernetes Provider Deployment\n255: \n256: The system SHALL deploy via standard Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service.\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: KubernetesProvider Initialization\n259: \n260: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider(namespace=\"default\", verbose=False)`\n261: - **WHEN** the provider is constructed\n262: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n263:   - Load kubeconfig via `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()`\n264:   - Initialize `AppsV1Api` for Deployment management\n265:   - Initialize `CoreV1Api` for Service and Namespace management\n266:   - Set namespace to `\"default\"` or provided value\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: Deploy Agent with Deployment and Service\n269: \n270: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` is called\n271: - **WHEN** deployment proceeds\n272: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n273:   - Call `_create_deployment()` to create Deployment\n274:   - Call `_create_service()` to create NodePort Service\n275:   - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready()` with timeout `120`\n276:   - Return result dict with `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url`\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: Create Deployment\n279: \n280: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_deployment()` is called\n281: - **WHEN** Deployment is created\n282: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n283:   - Set Deployment name via `_sanitize_name(agent_name)`\n284:   - Set `spec.replicas` to provided value or `1`\n285:   - Set container image, port, and optional entrypoint command\n286:   - Add `env_vars` to container spec if provided\n287:   - Set `selector.matchLabels` and `template.metadata.labels` to `{\"app\": sanitized_name}`\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: Create NodePort Service\n290: \n291: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_service()` is called\n292: - **WHEN** Service is created\n293: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n294:   - Set Service type to `NodePort`\n295:   - Set port to `metadata.port`\n296:   - Set `nodePort` to provided value if within range `30000-32767`\n297:   - Raise `ValueError` if `node_port` is outside valid range\n298:   - Allow Kubernetes to auto-assign NodePort if `node_port` is `None`\n299: \n300: #### Scenario: Wait for Deployment Ready\n301: \n302: - **GIVEN** deployment is created\n303: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120)` runs\n304: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n305:   - Poll deployment status every 2 seconds\n306:   - Check `status.availableReplicas == spec.replicas`\n307:   - Raise `TimeoutError` if timeout exceeded before ready\n308:   - Log progress in verbose mode\n309: \n310: #### Scenario: Deployment Readiness Failure\n311: \n312: - **GIVEN** deployment fails to become ready within timeout\n313: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready()` exceeds timeout\n314: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n315:   - Raise `RuntimeError` with deployment failure message\n316:   - Record error in metadata before raising\n317: \n318: #### Scenario: Delete Agent Resources\n319: \n320: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent(agent_name)` is called\n321: - **WHEN** deletion proceeds\n322: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n323:   - Delete Deployment via `delete_deployment()`\n324:   - Delete Service via `delete_service()`\n325:   - Ignore 404 errors for individual resources\n326:   - Return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}`\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ### Requirement: Metadata Update After Publish\n331: \n332: The system SHALL persist deployment information to metadata YAML.\n333: \n334: #### Scenario: Update Publish Metadata\n335: \n336: - **GIVEN** deployment completes successfully\n337: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata()` runs\n338: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n339:   - Update `metadata.agent_id` from deployment result\n340:   - Update `metadata.agent_endpoint` from deployment result\n341:   - Update `metadata.k8s_deployment` with deployment info dict\n342:   - Save metadata via `MetadataService.save_metadata()`\n343: \n344: #### Scenario: k8s_deployment Field Structure\n345: \n346: - **GIVEN** metadata is updated after publish\n347: - **WHEN** `k8s_deployment` field is set\n348: - **THEN** the field SHALL contain:\n349:   - `type`: `\"AgentRuntime\"` for agentcube provider or `\"Deployment\"` for k8s provider\n350:   - `deployment_name`: sanitized deployment name\n351:   - `service_name`: sanitized service name (k8s provider)\n352:   - `namespace`: deployment namespace\n353:   - `replicas`: replica count\n354:   - `node_port`: NodePort number (k8s provider)\n355:   - `service_url`: `http://localhost:{node_port}` (k8s provider)\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Record Error in Metadata on Failure\n358: \n359: - **GIVEN** deployment fails\n360: - **WHEN** error is recorded before raising\n361: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n362:   - Set `k8s_deployment.error` to error message\n363:   - Set `k8s_deployment.status` to `\"error\"`\n364:   - Save metadata before raising exception\n365: \n366: ---\n367: \n368: ### Requirement: Namespace Configuration\n369: \n370: The system SHALL support namespace configuration via CLI option.\n371: \n372: #### Scenario: Use Specified Namespace\n373: \n374: - **GIVEN** `--namespace my-namespace` is provided\n375: - **WHEN** provider is initialized\n376: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n377:   - Pass namespace to `KubernetesProvider` or `AgentCubeProvider`\n378:   - Create resources in specified namespace\n379: \n380: #### Scenario: Default Namespace\n381: \n382: - **GIVEN** `--namespace` is not provided\n383: - **WHEN** provider is initialized\n384: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n385:   - Use namespace from `metadata.k8s_deployment.namespace` if exists\n386:   - Use `\"default\"` as fallback\n387: \n388: ---\n389: \n390: ### Requirement: Replicas Configuration\n391: \n392: The system SHALL support replica count configuration.\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: Use Specified Replicas\n395: \n396: - **GIVEN** `--replicas 3` is provided\n397: - **WHEN** Kubernetes Deployment is created\n398: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be set to `3`\n399: \n400: #### Scenario: Default Replicas\n401: \n402: - **GIVEN** `--replicas` is not provided\n403: - **WHEN** Kubernetes Deployment is created\n404: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL default to `1`\n405: \n406: ---\n407: \n408: ### Requirement: NodePort Configuration\n409: \n410: The system SHALL support NodePort specification for Kubernetes Service.\n411: \n412: #### Scenario: Use Specified NodePort\n413: \n414: - **GIVEN** `--node-port 30080` is provided\n415: - **WHEN** Kubernetes Service is created\n416: - **THEN** `spec.ports[0].nodePort` SHALL be set to `30080`\n417: \n418: #### Scenario: NodePort Range Validation\n419: \n420: - **GIVEN** `--node-port 20000` is provided (outside range)\n421: - **WHEN** `_create_service()` validates\n422: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating NodePort must be in range `30000-32767`\n423: \n424: #### Scenario: Auto-assign NodePort\n425: \n426: - **GIVEN** `--node-port` is not provided\n427: - **WHEN** Kubernetes Service is created\n428: - **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL auto-assign a NodePort within valid range\n429: \n430: ---\n431: \n432: ### Requirement: Version Override\n433: \n434: The system SHALL support version string override.\n435: \n436: #### Scenario: Override Version via CLI\n437: \n438: - **GIVEN** `--version v1.0.0` is provided\n439: - **WHEN** metadata is updated before publish\n440: - **THEN** `metadata.version` SHALL be set to `\"v1.0.0\"`\n441: \n442: #### Scenario: Use Metadata Version\n443: \n444: - **GIVEN** `--version` is not provided and metadata has `version`\n445: - **WHEN** image is tagged or pushed\n446: - **THEN** the system SHALL use existing `metadata.version`\n447: \n448: ---\n449: \n450: ### Requirement: Registry Credentials\n451: \n452: The system SHALL support registry authentication for image push.\n453: \n454: #### Scenario: Push Image with Credentials\n455: \n456: - **GIVEN** `--image-username` and `--image-password` are provided\n457: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image()` runs\n458: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n459:   - Call `_docker_login_sdk()` with credentials\n460:   - Login to registry before push\n461:   - Stream push logs in verbose mode\n462: \n463: #### Scenario: Push Image without Credentials\n464: \n465: - **GIVEN** `--image-username` and `--image-password` are not provided\n466: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image()` runs\n467: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n468:   - Skip login step\n469:   - Attempt push assuming pre-authenticated Docker client\n470:   - Log warning if push fails due to auth\n471: \n472: #### Scenario: Docker Login SDK Method\n473: \n474: - **GIVEN** `DockerService._docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password)` is called\n475: - **WHEN** login executes\n476: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n477:   - Use `docker.from_env().login()` method\n478:   - Handle login failure gracefully\n479:   - Log success/failure message\n480: \n481: ---\n482: \n483: ### Requirement: Image Tag and Retag\n484: \n485: The system SHALL handle image tagging and retagging for registry push.\n486: \n487: #### Scenario: Tag Image for Registry\n488: \n489: - **GIVEN** local image `{agent_name}:latest`\n490: - **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image()` prepares for push\n491: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n492:   - Tag image as `{registry_url}/{agent_name}:{version}`\n493:   - Call `_tag_image_sdk()` for Docker SDK tagging\n494: \n495: #### Scenario: Tag Image SDK Method\n496: \n497: - **GIVEN** `DockerService._tag_image_sdk(source_image, target_image)` is called\n498: - **WHEN** tagging executes\n499: - **THEN** `docker_client.images.get(source_image).tag(target_image)` SHALL be called\n500: \n501: ---\n502: \n503: ### Requirement: Error Handling Patterns\n504: \n505: The system SHALL handle errors with appropriate messages and metadata updates.\n506: \n507: #### Scenario: Kubernetes Cluster Unreachable\n508: \n509: - **GIVEN** kubeconfig cannot connect to cluster\n510: - **WHEN** provider initialization runs\n511: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with message indicating cluster unreachable\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD Not Installed\n514: \n515: - **GIVEN** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` CRD does not exist\n516: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` attempts CR creation\n517: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n518:   - Catch API exception for CRD not found\n519:   - Raise `ValueError` indicating AgentCube CRD must be installed\n520: \n521: #### Scenario: Image Push Auth Failure\n522: \n523: - **GIVEN** registry credentials are invalid\n524: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image()` attempts push\n525: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n526:   - Catch Docker API exception\n527:   - Raise `RuntimeError` with auth failure message\n528:   - Log detailed error in verbose mode\n529: \n530: ---\n531: \n532: ### Requirement: Verbose Logging\n533: \n534: The system SHALL enable detailed logging when `--verbose` is passed.\n535: \n536: #### Scenario: Verbose Logging During Publish\n537: \n538: - **GIVEN** `--verbose` is passed to publish command\n539: - **WHEN** publish runs\n540: - **THEN** `PublishRuntime` SHALL:\n541:   - Log each step: metadata loading, image preparation, deployment\n542:   - Log Kubernetes API calls and responses\n543:   - Log Docker push progress\n544:   - Include intermediate results in logs\n545: \n546: ---\n547: \n548: ### Requirement: Progress Indicator During Publish\n549: \n550: The system SHALL display a progress spinner during publish operations.\n551: \n552: #### Scenario: Rich Progress Spinner Display\n553: \n554: - **GIVEN** the publish command is executing\n555: - **WHEN** operations like image push and deployment run\n556: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display a Rich Progress spinner with descriptive text (e.g., \"Publishing agent to Kubernetes...\")\n557: \n558: ---\n559: \n560: ### Requirement: Publish Result Structure\n561: \n562: The system SHALL return a structured result from `PublishRuntime.publish`.\n563: \n564: #### Scenario: Return Publish Result Dictionary\n565: \n566: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` completes successfully\n567: - **WHEN** the method returns\n568: - **THEN** the result SHALL be a `Dict[str, Any]` containing:\n569:   - `agent_name`: the resolved agent name\n570:   - `agent_id`: assigned agent ID (agentcube provider)\n571:   - `agent_endpoint`: endpoint URL for invoking agent\n572:   - `deployment_type`: `\"AgentRuntime\"` or `\"Deployment\"`\n573:   - `namespace`: deployment namespace\n574:   - `k8s_deployment`: full deployment info dict\n575: \n576: ---\n577: \n578: ### Requirement: Provider Selection Validation\n579: \n580: The system SHALL validate provider selection.\n581: \n582: #### Scenario: Valid Provider Values\n583: \n584: - **GIVEN** `--provider agentcube` or `--provider k8s` is provided\n585: - **WHEN** provider is validated\n586: - **THEN** the system SHALL accept the value and proceed\n587: \n588: #### Scenario: Invalid Provider Value\n589: \n590: - **GIVEN** `--provider helm` is provided\n591: - **WHEN** provider is validated\n592: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating valid providers are `agentcube` and `k8s`\n593: \n594: ---\n595: \n596: ### Requirement: Publish Command Help Text\n597: \n598: The system SHALL provide help text for all publish command options.\n599: \n600: #### Scenario: Publish Command Help Display\n601: \n602: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --help`\n603: - **WHEN** the help is displayed\n604: - **THEN** Typer SHALL show:\n605:   - Command description\n606:   - All options with their names, types, defaults, and help strings\n607:   - Usage examples if configured\n608: \n609: ---\n610: \n611: ### Requirement: Workspace Path Resolution\n612: \n613: The system SHALL resolve the workspace path to an absolute path.\n614: \n615: #### Scenario: Resolve Relative Workspace Path\n616: \n617: - **GIVEN** `workspace = \".\"` (relative path)\n618: - **WHEN** the publish command processes the workspace\n619: - **THEN** the system SHALL resolve it to an absolute path using `Path(workspace).resolve()`\n620: \n621: ---\n622: \n623: ### Requirement: Kubernetes Python SDK Integration\n624: \n625: The system SHALL use kubernetes Python client for API interactions.\n626: \n627: #### Scenario: Load Kubeconfig\n628: \n629: - **GIVEN** `kubeconfig` is not specified\n630: - **WHEN** provider initializes\n631: - **THEN** `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()` SHALL be called to load from `~/.kube/config`\n632: \n633: #### Scenario: Load Explicit Kubeconfig\n634: \n635: - **GIVEN** `kubeconfig` path is specified\n636: - **WHEN** provider initializes\n637: - **THEN** `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)` SHALL be called\n638: \n639: ---\n640: \n641: ## Constants Summary\n642: \n643: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n644: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n645: | Default namespace | `\"default\"` | `k8s_provider.py`, `agentcube_provider.py` | Fallback namespace for deployments |\n646: | Default replicas | `1` | `k8s_provider.py` | Default replica count for Deployment |\n647: | Deployment timeout | `120` | `k8s_provider.py` | Seconds to wait for deployment readiness |\n648: | Poll interval | `2` | `k8s_provider.py` | Seconds between readiness checks |\n649: | NodePort min | `30000` | `k8s_provider.py` | Minimum valid NodePort |\n650: | NodePort max | `32767` | `k8s_provider.py` | Maximum valid NodePort |\n651: | Session timeout | `\"15m\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime session timeout |\n652: | Max session duration | `\"8h\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime max session duration |\n653: | ImagePullSecret | `\"default-secret\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default image pull secret name |\n654: | CR API group | `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API group |\n655: | CR API version | `\"v1alpha1\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API version |\n656: | CR plural | `\"agentruntimes\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR plural name |\n657: \n658: ---\n659: \n660: ## Dependencies Summary\n661: \n662: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n663: |---------|---------|---------|\n664: | `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n665: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n666: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n667: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push operations |\n668: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes Python client for Deployment/Service/CR management (optional `[k8s]` dependency) |\n669: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and error display |\n670: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future cloud integration |\n671: | `pathlib` | (stdlib) | Path resolution |\n672: \n673: ---\n674: \n675: ## File Changes Summary\n676: \n677: | File | Action | Description |\n678: |------|--------|-------------|\n679: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Extend | Add `publish` Typer command with all CLI options |\n680: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Create | `PublishRuntime` class with publish orchestration |\n681: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | Create | `KubernetesProvider` for Deployment/Service management |\n682: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | Create | `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR deployment |\n683: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Extend | Add `push_image`, `_docker_login_sdk`, `_tag_image_sdk` methods |\n684: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Extend | Handle `k8s_deployment` and `agent_id` fields |\n685: | `tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | Create | Unit tests for PublishRuntime |\n686: | `tests/test_k8s_provider.py` | Create | Unit tests for KubernetesProvider |\n687: | `tests/test_agentcube_provider.py` | Create | Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider |\n688: \n689: ---\n690: \n691: ## References\n692: \n693: - AR-021 — CLI build command (prerequisite for built image)\n694: - AR-023 — CLI invoke command\n695: - AR-024 — CLI status command\n696: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n697: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification\n698: - deployment/spec.md — Kubernetes deployment patterns\n699: - Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n700: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n701: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n702: \n703: ---\n704: \n705: ## Validation Checklist\n706: \n707: - [ ] Publish command registered in Typer app with correct options\n708: - [ ] Options have correct types and defaults matching spec\n709: - [ ] PublishRuntime orchestrates validation, image prep, deployment, metadata update\n710: - [ ] AgentCube provider validates router_url and workload_manager_url\n711: - [ ] Kubernetes provider creates Deployment and NodePort Service\n712: - [ ] NodePort range validation (30000-32767) implemented\n713: - [ ] wait_for_deployment_ready with 120s timeout implemented\n714: - [ ] AgentRuntime CR created with correct API group/version/plural\n715: - [ ] CR includes sessionTimeout=\"15m\", maxSessionDuration=\"8h\"\n716: - [ ] Image push with Docker SDK and registry credentials\n717: - [ ] Metadata updated with agent_id, agent_endpoint, k8s_deployment\n718: - [ ] Error handling updates metadata before raising\n719: - [ ] Verbose mode enables detailed logging\n720: - [ ] Rich Progress spinner displayed during execution\n721: - [ ] Provider selection validation (agentcube/k8s)\n722: - [ ] Namespace support from CLI option or metadata\n723: - [ ] Replicas and NodePort configuration supported\n724: - [ ] Version override via CLI option\n725: - [ ] Unit tests for all components with mocked K8s/Docker APIs\n\n(End of file - total 725 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Publish Command Entry Point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `publish` subcommand via Typer application to deploy agents to Kubernetes with provider selection.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871385535,"end":1775871385553}}}}
