{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871531874,"sessionID":"ses_285d19579ffenKhkYlggxpkabA","part":{"id":"prt_d7a311ad90010fFYmU3keDKizT","messageID":"msg_d7a2ee014001kU3POk0CtOHvTb","sessionID":"ses_285d19579ffenKhkYlggxpkabA","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-ec633d3282f140aab382c94f27eb6fa6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","content":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe `publish` command orchestrates agent deployment to Kubernetes via two providers:\n- **agentcube**: Creates `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR) for Volcano AgentCube integration\n- **k8s**: Creates standard Kubernetes `Deployment` + `NodePort Service`\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         User CLI                                 │\n│  kubectl-agentcube publish -f ./agent --provider k8s            │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     CLI Layer (main.py)                          │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ Typer app.publish()                                       │   │\n│  │  - Parse CLI options                                      │   │\n│  │  - Create PublishRuntime                                  │   │\n│  │  - Handle errors (_handle_error)                          │   │\n│  │  - Display Rich Progress spinner                          │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Runtime Layer                                 │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ PublishRuntime.publish()                                  │   │\n│  │  1. Load metadata (MetadataService)                       │   │\n│  │  2. Apply option overrides                                │   │\n│  │  3. Prepare image (_prepare_image_for_publishing)         │   │\n│  │  4. Deploy via provider                                   │   │\n│  │  5. Update metadata                                       │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n              ┌───────────────┼───────────────┐\n              ▼               ▼               ▼\n┌─────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐\n│ AgentCube       │ │ Kubernetes      │ │ Docker          │\n│ Provider        │ │ Provider        │ │ Service         │\n│ (CR API)        │ │ (Deployment)    │ │ (Push)          │\n└─────────────────┘ └─────────────────┘ └─────────────────┘\n              │               │               │\n              ▼               ▼               ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Kubernetes Cluster                            │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │ AgentRuntime CR  │  │ Deployment + NodePort Service    │     │\n│  │ (agentcube)      │  │ (k8s)                            │     │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────────────┘     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\nPublishRuntime\n├── MetadataService (load/save metadata)\n├── DockerService (push_image, login, tag)\n├── Provider Selection\n│   ├── AgentCubeProvider (provider=\"agentcube\")\n│   │   ├── CustomObjectsApi (CR create/patch)\n│   │   ├── CoreV1Api (namespace)\n│   │   └── _sanitize_name()\n│   │   └── _ensure_namespace()\n│   └── KubernetesProvider (provider=\"k8s\")\n│       ├── AppsV1Api (Deployment)\n│       ├── CoreV1Api (Service, Namespace)\n│       ├── _create_deployment()\n│       ├── _create_service()\n│       ├── wait_for_deployment_ready()\n│       └── _sanitize_name()\n└── _update_publish_metadata()\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### AgentMetadata Extensions (Pydantic BaseModel)\n\n```python\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    agent_name: str\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    language: str = \"python\"\n    entrypoint: str\n    port: int = 8080\n    build_mode: str = \"local\"\n    region: Optional[str] = None\n    version: Optional[str] = None\n    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n    auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n    router_url: Optional[str] = None\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None\n    agent_id: Optional[str] = None       # NEW: Assigned by AgentCube\n    session_id: Optional[str] = None\n    k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None  # NEW: Deployment info\n\n    @validator(\"language\")\n    def validate_language(cls, v):\n        allowed = [\"python\", \"java\"]\n        if v.lower() not in allowed:\n            raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {allowed}\")\n        return v.lower()\n\n    @validator(\"build_mode\")\n    def validate_build_mode(cls, v):\n        allowed = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n        if v.lower() not in allowed:\n            raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {allowed}\")\n        return v.lower()\n\n    @validator(\"port\")\n    def validate_port(cls, v):\n        if not (1 <= v <= 65535):\n            raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n        return v\n```\n\n### k8s_deployment Field Structure\n\n```python\nk8s_deployment: Dict[str, Any] = {\n    \"type\": \"AgentRuntime\" | \"Deployment\",\n    \"deployment_name\": str,\n    \"service_name\": str,           # k8s provider only\n    \"namespace\": str,\n    \"replicas\": int,\n    \"node_port\": int,              # k8s provider only\n    \"service_url\": str,            # k8s provider only: \"http://localhost:{node_port}\"\n    \"agent_id\": str,               # agentcube provider only\n    \"status\": \"created\" | \"ready\" | \"error\",\n    \"error\": Optional[str],        # Set on failure\n}\n```\n\n### PublishOptions (Internal)\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass PublishOptions:\n    workspace: Path\n    version: Optional[str] = None\n    image_url: Optional[str] = None\n    image_username: Optional[str] = None\n    image_password: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    region: Optional[str] = None\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None\n    provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n    node_port: Optional[int] = None\n    replicas: Optional[int] = None\n    namespace: Optional[str] = None\n    verbose: bool = False\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Typer Command Interface\n\n```python\n@app.command()\ndef publish(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", \n        help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\",\n        help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n    image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\",\n        help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n    image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\",\n        help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n    image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\",\n        help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\",\n        help=\"Agent description\"),\n    region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\",\n        help=\"Deployment region\"),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\",\n        help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\",\n        help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n    node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\",\n        help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n    replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\",\n        help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n    namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\",\n        help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\",\n        help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Deploy agent to Kubernetes cluster.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n        runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n        options = {\n            \"version\": version,\n            \"image_url\": image_url,\n            \"image_username\": image_username,\n            \"image_password\": image_password,\n            \"description\": description,\n            \"region\": region,\n            \"cloud_provider\": cloud_provider,\n            \"node_port\": node_port,\n            \"replicas\": replicas,\n            \"namespace\": namespace,\n        }\n        with Progress(SpinnerColumn(), TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\")) as progress:\n            task = progress.add_task(\"Publishing agent to Kubernetes...\", total=None)\n            result = runtime.publish(workspace_path, **options)\n            progress.remove_task(task)\n        \n        console.print(f\"[green]Successfully published agent![/green]\")\n        console.print(f\"  Agent Name: {result['agent_name']}\")\n        console.print(f\"  Agent ID: {result.get('agent_id', 'N/A')}\")\n        console.print(f\"  Endpoint: {result['agent_endpoint']}\")\n        console.print(f\"  Deployment Type: {result['deployment_type']}\")\n        console.print(f\"  Namespace: {result['namespace']}\")\n        \n    except Exception as e:\n        _handle_error(e, \"publishing agent\", verbose)\n```\n\n### PublishRuntime Contract\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider\n        self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n        self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n        \n        if provider == \"k8s\":\n            self.k8s_provider = KubernetesProvider(verbose=verbose)\n        elif provider == \"agentcube\":\n            self.agentcube_provider = AgentCubeProvider(verbose=verbose)\n        else:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Invalid provider: {provider}. Must be 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\")\n\n    def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Orchestrates the publish workflow.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Dict containing agent_name, agent_id, agent_endpoint, deployment_type, namespace, k8s_deployment\n        \"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Deploy via AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Deploy via standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Return image URL ready for deployment.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Push local Docker image to registry.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Use cloud-built image URL.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Persist deployment info to metadata YAML.\"\"\"\n        ...\n```\n\n### AgentCubeProvider Contract\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    CR_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n    CR_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\n    CR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None:\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        \n        if kubeconfig:\n            kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n        else:\n            kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()\n        \n        self.custom_api = kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi()\n        self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()\n\n    def deploy_agent_runtime(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Create or patch AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Create namespace if not exists.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Convert to lowercase DNS-compliant name (max 63 chars).\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n        \"\"\"Retrieve AgentRuntime CR status.\"\"\"\n        ...\n```\n\n### KubernetesProvider Contract\n\n```python\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    NODE_PORT_MIN = 30000\n    NODE_PORT_MAX = 32767\n    DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120\n    POLL_INTERVAL = 2\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None:\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        \n        if kubeconfig:\n            kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n        else:\n            kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()\n        \n        self.apps_api = kubernetes.client.AppsV1Api()\n        self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()\n\n    def deploy_agent(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        replicas: int = 1,\n        node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Create Deployment + NodePort Service and wait for ready.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def _create_deployment(\n        self,\n        name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str],\n        replicas: int,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Create Kubernetes Deployment.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Create NodePort Service.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Poll deployment status until ready or timeout.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Get Deployment and Service status.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Delete Deployment and Service.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Create namespace if not exists.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\n    def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Convert to lowercase DNS-compliant name (max 63 chars).\"\"\"\n        ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories\n\n| Category | Exception Type | Message Pattern | Recovery |\n|----------|----------------|-----------------|----------|\n| Metadata Missing | `ValueError` | `Missing required field: {field} in agent_metadata.yaml` | User must add field |\n| Provider Invalid | `ValueError` | `Invalid provider: {value}. Must be 'agentcube' or 'k8s'` | Use valid provider |\n| Image URL Missing | `ValueError` | `--image-url is required for local build mode` | Provide image URL |\n| Router URL Missing | `ValueError` | `router_url is required for agentcube provider in agent_metadata.yaml` | Add router_url |\n| Workload Manager Missing | `ValueError` | `workload_manager_url is required for agentcube provider` | Add workload_manager_url |\n| NodePort Invalid | `ValueError` | `NodePort must be in range 30000-32767` | Use valid NodePort |\n| Docker Unavailable | `RuntimeError` | `Docker is not available or not running` | Start Docker |\n| Docker Push Failed | `RuntimeError` | `Failed to push image: {details}` | Check credentials |\n| K8s Unreachable | `RuntimeError` | `Kubernetes cluster is unreachable` | Check kubeconfig |\n| CRD Not Found | `ValueError` | `AgentRuntime CRD not installed. Install Volcano AgentCube CRDs` | Install CRDs |\n| Deployment Timeout | `TimeoutError` | `Deployment {name} not ready after {timeout}s` | Check pod logs |\n| Registry Auth Failed | `RuntimeError` | `Registry authentication failed: {details}` | Check credentials |\n\n### Error Handling Pattern\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Print error and exit with code 1.\"\"\"\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n    if verbose:\n        console.print_exception()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n### Metadata Error Recording\n\n```python\ndef _record_error_in_metadata(workspace_path: Path, error_msg: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Record error in metadata before raising exception.\"\"\"\n    metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n    metadata.k8s_deployment = {\n        \"status\": \"error\",\n        \"error\": error_msg,\n    }\n    self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test File | Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | PublishRuntime orchestration, option overrides, provider selection |\n| `tests/test_k8s_provider.py` | KubernetesProvider methods with mocked K8s API |\n| `tests/test_agentcube_provider.py` | AgentCubeProvider CR creation/patch with mocked API |\n| `tests/test_docker_service.py` | push_image, login, tag methods |\n\n### Mock Strategy\n\n```python\n# Kubernetes API Mock\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_k8s_api():\n    with patch(\"kubernetes.client.AppsV1Api\") as mock_apps:\n        with patch(\"kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api\") as mock_core:\n            mock_apps.return_value.create_deployment.return_value = ...\n            mock_core.return_value.create_namespaced_service.return_value = ...\n            yield mock_apps, mock_core\n\n# AgentRuntime CR Mock\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_custom_api():\n    with patch(\"kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi\") as mock_custom:\n        mock_custom.return_value.create_custom_object.return_value = {\n            \"metadata\": {\"name\": \"test-agent\"},\n            \"status\": {\"agentEndpoint\": \"http://test\"},\n        }\n        yield mock_custom\n\n# Docker Mock\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_docker():\n    with patch(\"docker.from_env\") as mock_client:\n        mock_client.return_value.images.push.return_value = [...]\n        yield mock_client\n```\n\n### Test Cases\n\n| Test Case | Scenario |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `test_publish_agentcube_success` | Valid metadata, agentcube provider, CR created |\n| `test_publish_k8s_success` | Valid metadata, k8s provider, Deployment + Service created |\n| `test_publish_missing_router_url` | agentcube provider without router_url raises ValueError |\n| `test_publish_missing_workload_manager` | agentcube provider without workload_manager_url raises ValueError |\n| `test_publish_invalid_provider` | Invalid provider raises ValueError |\n| `test_publish_image_url_required_local` | Local build mode without image_url raises ValueError |\n| `test_publish_node_port_out_of_range` | NodePort outside 30000-32767 raises ValueError |\n| `test_publish_deployment_timeout` | Deployment not ready after 120s raises TimeoutError |\n| `test_publish_metadata_update` | Metadata saved with agent_id and k8s_deployment |\n| `test_publish_error_metadata_update` | Error recorded in metadata before exception |\n| `test_k8s_provider_sanitize_name` | Name sanitized to DNS-compliant format |\n| `test_agentcube_provider_sanitize_name` | CR name sanitized |\n| `test_agentcube_provider_patch_existing_cr` | Patch instead of create for existing CR |\n| `test_docker_push_with_credentials` | Login + push with username/password |\n| `test_docker_push_without_credentials` | Push without login (pre-authenticated) |\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                    # Package exports\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   └── main.py                    # Typer app + publish command\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── pack_runtime.py            # (AR-020)\n│   │   ├── build_runtime.py           # (AR-021)\n│   │   ├── publish_runtime.py         # NEW: PublishRuntime\n│   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py          # (AR-023)\n│   │   └── status_runtime.py          # (AR-024)\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── metadata_service.py        # Load/save metadata\n│   │   ├── docker_service.py          # EXTEND: push_image, login, tag\n│   │   ├── k8s_provider.py            # NEW: KubernetesProvider\n│   │   └── agentcube_provider.py      # NEW: AgentCubeProvider\n│   └── models/\n│       ├── __init__.py\n│       └── pack_models.py             # MetadataOptions\n├── tests/\n│   ├── test_publish_runtime.py        # NEW\n│   ├── test_k8s_provider.py           # NEW\n│   ├── test_agentcube_provider.py     # NEW\n│   └── test_docker_service.py         # EXTEND\n├── pyproject.toml                     # Dependencies\n└── examples/\n    └── hello-agent/\n        ├── main.py\n        └── agent_metadata.yaml        # Example metadata\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Runtime Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n| `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n| `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n| `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push operations |\n| `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes Python client (optional `[k8s]` extras) |\n| `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and error display |\n| `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future cloud integration |\n| `pathlib` | (stdlib) | Path resolution |\n\n### pyproject.toml Optional Dependencies\n\n```toml\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nk8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\ndev = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n    \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n    \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n    \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n]\ntest = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n    \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| `CR_GROUP` | `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API group |\n| `CR_VERSION` | `\"v1alpha1\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API version |\n| `CR_PLURAL` | `\"agentruntimes\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR plural name |\n| `SESSION_TIMEOUT` | `\"15m\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default session timeout |\n| `MAX_SESSION_DURATION` | `\"8h\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default max session duration |\n| `DEFAULT_SECRET` | `\"default-secret\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default imagePullSecret |\n| `NODE_PORT_MIN` | `30000` | `k8s_provider.py` | Minimum valid NodePort |\n| `NODE_PORT_MAX` | `32767` | `k8s_provider.py` | Maximum valid NodePort |\n| `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | `120` | `k8s_provider.py` | Deployment readiness timeout |\n| `POLL_INTERVAL` | `2` | `k8s_provider.py` | Status poll interval (seconds) |\n\n### AgentRuntime CR Template\n\n```python\ncr_body = {\n    \"apiVersion\": f\"{self.CR_GROUP}/{self.CR_VERSION}\",\n    \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n    \"metadata\": {\n        \"name\": sanitized_name,\n        \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n    },\n    \"spec\": {\n        \"image\": image_url,\n        \"port\": port,\n        \"entrypoint\": entrypoint,\n        \"sessionTimeout\": \"15m\",\n        \"maxSessionDuration\": \"8h\",\n        \"imagePullSecrets\": [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}],\n        \"env\": [\n            {\"name\": \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\", \"value\": workload_manager_url},\n            {\"name\": \"ROUTER_URL\", \"value\": router_url},\n        ],\n        \"readinessProbe\": {\n            \"httpGet\": {\n                \"path\": readiness_probe_path or \"/health\",\n                \"port\": readiness_probe_port or port,\n            },\n        },\n    },\n}\n```\n\n### Kubernetes Deployment Template\n\n```python\ndeployment_body = {\n    \"apiVersion\": \"apps/v1\",\n    \"kind\": \"Deployment\",\n    \"metadata\": {\n        \"name\": sanitized_name,\n        \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n        \"labels\": {\"app\": sanitized_name},\n    },\n    \"spec\": {\n        \"replicas\": replicas,\n        \"selector\": {\"matchLabels\": {\"app\": sanitized_name}},\n        \"template\": {\n            \"metadata\": {\"labels\": {\"app\": sanitized_name}},\n            \"spec\": {\n                \"containers\": [{\n                    \"name\": sanitized_name,\n                    \"image\": image_url,\n                    \"ports\": [{\"containerPort\": port}],\n                    \"env\": [{\"name\": k, \"value\": v} for k, v in (env_vars or {}).items()],\n                }],\n            },\n        },\n    },\n}\n```\n\n### NodePort Service Template\n\n```python\nservice_body = {\n    \"apiVersion\": \"v1\",\n    \"kind\": \"Service\",\n    \"metadata\": {\n        \"name\": sanitized_name,\n        \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n    },\n    \"spec\": {\n        \"type\": \"NodePort\",\n        \"selector\": {\"app\": sanitized_name},\n        \"ports\": [{\n            \"port\": port,\n            \"targetPort\": port,\n            \"nodePort\": node_port,  # Optional, K8s auto-assigns if None\n        }],\n    },\n}\n```\n\n### Name Sanitization Algorithm\n\n```python\ndef _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Convert to lowercase DNS-compliant name (max 63 chars).\n    Rules:\n    - Lowercase only\n    - Replace non-alphanumeric with '-'\n    - Truncate to 63 characters\n    - Remove leading/trailing '-'\n    \"\"\"\n    sanitized = name.lower()\n    sanitized = re.sub(r\"[^a-z0-9-]\", \"-\", sanitized)\n    sanitized = re.sub(r\"-+\", \"-\", sanitized)\n    sanitized = sanitized.strip(\"-\")\n    return sanitized[:63]\n```\n\n### Wait for Deployment Ready Algorithm\n\n```python\ndef wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n    start = time.time()\n    while time.time() - start < timeout:\n        deployment = self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment(name, self.namespace)\n        if deployment.status.available_replicas == deployment.spec.replicas:\n            return\n        time.sleep(self.POLL_INTERVAL)\n    raise TimeoutError(f\"Deployment {name} not ready after {timeout}s\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n- cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (publish command requirements)\n- deployment/spec.md — Kubernetes deployment patterns\n- python-sdk/spec.md — AgentRuntimeClient integration\n- AR-021 — CLI build command (prerequisite for built image)\n- AR-023 — CLI invoke command\n- AR-024 — CLI status command\n- Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n- Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n- Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n- Volcano AgentCube CRD: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775871531823,"end":1775871531871}}}}
